Replaces: grub-efi-amd64
Provides: grub-efi-amd64
Description: GRUB2 EFI binary for amd64 with BLS and Secure Boot support
 Provides a GRUB2 EFI binary (grubx64.efi) compiled from the Fedora
 rhboot/grub2 fork with BLS (Boot Loader Specification) support required
 by ostree and bootc, signed with the debian-bootc Secure Boot signing key.
 .
 The binary is verified by the shim bootloader through the MOK (Machine
 Owner Key) mechanism. The signing certificate is included at
 /usr/share/debian-bootc/sb_signing.crt and automatically queued for MOK
 enrollment via the package postinst script. Enrollment confirmation is
 required at the MokManager screen on the next reboot.
